    "translations": {
      "en": {
        "summary": "In this hadith from al-Amali of Shaykh al-Saduq, Imam Ali (AS) identifies five occasions when supplication is most readily accepted by Allah: during Quran recitation, at the adhan, when rain falls, when armies meet for battle, and at the cry of the oppressed. The teaching emphasizes that the du'a of the oppressed ascends directly to the Throne of Allah without any barrier, highlighting the gravity of oppression in Islamic ethics.",
        "key_terms": {
          "الدعاء": "supplication (du'a) - calling upon Allah with requests and devotion",
          "الغيث": "rain - in Islamic tradition, rain is a sign of divine mercy",
          "الشهادة": "martyrdom - dying for the sake of faith",
          "المظلوم": "the oppressed one - whose supplication is never rejected",
          "حجاب": "barrier/veil - obstruction between the supplication and the Throne"
        },
        "seo_question": "What are the five best times for supplication according to Imam Ali?"
      },
